    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "everything just feels so loud and pointless. i look at my life and i see this massive, heavy debt of effort that led to nothing. it's like i've run a marathon for years only to realize there was no finish line, just more track. i'm just so desperate for some kind of peace, any kind of way to just... be at rest. like, is it really so wrong to just want to stop the noise? to just find a way to finally be still?",
